.TH VEK_L2SQ_U8 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_l2sq_u8 \- squared L2 distance between two uint8 vectors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "uint32_t vek_l2sq_u8(const uint8_t *" a ", const uint8_t *" b ", size_t " n ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_l2sq_u8 ()
computes the squared Euclidean (L2) distance between two unsigned 8-bit
integer vectors:
.PP
.RS
result = sum((a[i] - b[i])^2) for i = 0 to n-1
.RE
.PP
This is the squared distance, which avoids the square root computation. Use
.BR sqrt (3)
to obtain the actual L2 distance if needed.
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.I a
First input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I b
Second input vector. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I n
Number of elements. Must be greater than 0.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the squared L2 distance as a 32-bit unsigned integer.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
uint8_t a[] = {1, 2, 3};
uint8_t b[] = {4, 5, 6};
uint32_t result = vek_l2sq_u8(a, b, 3);  // 27
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_l2sq_f32 (3),
.BR vek_dot_u8 (3),
.BR vek_cosine_u8 (3)
